<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC19E1F81C227EB38D14EF5" blockId="13.[136,1452,1742,2093]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F81C227EB39BC4F81" box="[136,204,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Herbs</emphasis>
, ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F804827EB38374F80" box="[258,327,1742,1769]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="17.0">17 cm</quantity>
tall. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F80CA27EB389A4F81" box="[384,490,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Branches</emphasis>
green, cylindrical, costate. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F825527EA3A1D4F81" box="[799,877,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Leaves</emphasis>
opposite, sessile, discolorous, blades 1.5 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F841227EB3CD74F80" box="[1368,1447,1742,1769]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
, lanceolate, coriaceous, glabrous, attenuate at base, acute at apex, entire at margin. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F857327D73DBF4E65" box="[1081,1231,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Inflorescence</emphasis>
in terminal cymes, 1-flowered, peduncle 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F80C826333B754E58" box="[386,517,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.3">0.3–1.2 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F835826333B1E4E59" box="[530,622,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Flowers</emphasis>
homostylous, 4-merous, pedicel 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F82A126333D1E4E58" box="[1003,1134,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="0.8" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.4">0.4–1.2 cm</quantity>
; calyx 0.5 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F844D26333C294E58" box="[1287,1369,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
, green, winged, not keeled, tubular, glabrous; corolla yellowish, infundibuliform, tube 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F82BB261F3D5A4E3C" box="[1009,1066,1850,1877]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
, lobes 2 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F85D4261F3DA74E3C" box="[1182,1239,1850,1877]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
, at base obovate, at apex rounded; stamens 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F80C5267B38B94E10" box="[399,457,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
, isodynamous, adnate, conation 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F827E267A3A074E10" box="[820,887,1887,1913]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
; ovary 7 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F82BF267B3D474E10" box="[1013,1079,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, style ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F85EF267B3D844E10" box="[1189,1268,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
, stigma bilobed. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F81C226A639B24EF5" box="[136,194,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Fruit</emphasis>
septifragal capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354B9CEFFC19E1C81F726833AE84869" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC19E1C81F726833AE84869" blockId="13.[136,1452,1742,2093]" lastBlockId="14.[136,1452,158,509]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F81F72683389C4EA9" bold="true" box="[189,492,1958,1984]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC19E1F835A26833A644EA9" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1827" box="[528,788,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Schultesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crenuliflora">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F835A26833A644EA9" box="[528,788,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Schultesia crenuliflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in “campo rupestre” at altitudes above 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC19E1F840C26833CF94EA9" box="[1350,1417,1958,1984]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="900.0">900m</quantity>
, is considered in the list of rare species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC19E1F836726EF3A3D4E8D" author="Calio, M. F. A. &amp; Guimaraes, E. F." box="[557,845,1994,2020]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" pagination="185 - 186" refId="ref12762" refString="Calio, M. F. A. &amp; Guimaraes, E. F. (2009) Gentianaceae. In: Giulietti, A. M., Rapini, A., Andrade, M. J. G., Queiroz, L. P. &amp; Silva, J. M. C. (Eds.) Plantas raras do Brasil. Conservacao Internacional, Belo Horizonte. pp. 185 - 186." type="book chapter" year="2009">Calió &amp; Guimarães 2009</bibRefCitation>
), and is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC19E1F857A26EF3D014E8D" box="[1072,1137,1994,2020]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC19E1F85CB26EF3C134E8D" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[1153,1379,1994,2020]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F85A226EE3C514E8D" box="[1256,1313,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC19E1F842526EF38734160" author="Calio, M. F. A. &amp; Guimaraes, E. F. &amp; Saavedra, M. M. &amp; Melo, A." pageId="13" pageNumber="74" refId="ref12841" refString="Calio, M. F. A., Guimaraes, E. F., Saavedra, M. M. &amp; Melo, A. (2015) Gentianaceae. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 117 (accessed 7 January 2019)" type="url" year="2015">
Calió 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F81C226CA39B04161" box="[136,192,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
), being registered for the cities of Abaíra, Andaraí, Barra da Estiva, Ibicoara, Lençóis, Mucugê, Palmeiras, Piatã, Rio de Contas and Seabra (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC19E1F80B529373B924145" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[511,738,2066,2092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC19E1F832C29363BEE4145" box="[614,670,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). It is also considered vulnerable (VU) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC19E1F85E929373C5B4145" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge U. K." box="[1187,1323,2066,2092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" refId="ref15757" refString="IUCN (2020) The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, version 2020 - 1. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge U. K. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / (accessed 19 May 2020)" type="url" year="2020">IUCN 2020</bibRefCitation>
, CNCFlora 2014 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC29E1C818921BB38A749D1" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[195,471,158,184]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
b, Guimarães 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC29E1C801621BA38E449D1" box="[348,404,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution modeling analysis recovered high suitability for the occurrence of the species in the entire northern portion of the ER, allowing to infer the occurrence of the specie also for the Serra Geral de Licínio de Almeida (
<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC29E1C80DB21C338A34869" box="[401,467,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1815,1837]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,200,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1436,187,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Parque Municipal de Mucugê—Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil. Map of the study area, evidencing the location of PMM and other areas of the Espinhaço Range (ER) used for comparison in this study (A), “campo rupestre” phytophysiognomy (B). Photo B by Ariane Leite. Legend: (Lilac area) ER above 1000 m a.s.l." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424487/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC29E1C80AB21C33B464869" box="[481,566,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[444,1147,867,1622]" captionTargetId="figure-307@7.[434,1153,857,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Maps of occurrence with localities used for the species distribution modeling, showing the study area location within South America. Curtia diffusa (A), Macrocarpaea illecebrosa (B), Prepusa montana (C), Schultesia bahiensis (D), Schultesia crenuliflora (E), Schultesia minensis (F), Schultesia pachyphylla (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424489/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC29E1C830821C33BE94869" box="[578,665,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[341,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[340,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. Species of Gentianaceae from the Parque Municipal de Mucugê - Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil: Calolisianthus pedunculatus (A), Chelonanthus purpurascens (B), Curtia verticillaris (C), Curtia tenuifolia (D), Prepusa montana (E), Schultesia bahiensis (F), Schultesia crenuliflora (G), Schultesia pachyphylla (H). Scale bars:A: 2 cm; B: 1 cm; C: 0,5 cm; D: 0,5 cm; E: 2 cm; F–H: 1 cm. Photo A, B, E, F, G and H by Maria Luiza Silveira de Carvalho; C and D by Vinicius Dittrich and Gustavo Shimizu, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424491/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC29E1C83EF21C33B8B4869" box="[677,763,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[136,229,1180,1202]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1155]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[151,1436,190,1155]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Maps of environmental suitability of native/endemic species of Gentianaceae in the Espinhaço Range (ER): Curtia diffusa (A), Macrocarpaea illecebrosa (B), Prepusa montana (C), Schultesia bahiensis (D), Schultesia crenuliflora (E), Schultesia minensis (F), Schultesia pachyphylla (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424493/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
, Appendix 1).
</paragraph>
