<subSubSection id="C354B9CEFFC29E1C81F7202F3AE84895" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC29E1C81F7202F3BCB48DD" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC29E1C81F7202F384E484D" bold="true" box="[189,318,266,292]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Comments</emphasis>
:—It can be identified and differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC29E1C822F202F3D3D484D" authorityName="Guimaraes &amp; Fontella" authorityYear="2001" box="[869,1101,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Schultesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC29E1C822F202F3D3D484D" box="[869,1101,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Schultesia bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the coriaceous leaves (vs. chartaceous leaves) and internodes generally larger or equal to the size of the leaf (almost always smaller than internodes throughout the entire plant), and the yellowish corolla (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC29E1C83A620773ABD4805" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[748,973,338,364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC29E1C821820763AFA4805" box="[850,906,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Like 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC29E1C855220763DED4805" authorityName="Guimaraes &amp; Fontella" authorityYear="2001" box="[1048,1181,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Schultesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC29E1C855220763DED4805" box="[1048,1181,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">S. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species can vary in the amount of flowers, with up to 4 flowers being observed in each inflorescence and can be collected with fruits and flowers throughout the year (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC29E1C808720BF3BDF48DD" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[461,687,410,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC29E1C837920BE3B1B48DD" box="[563,619,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
